critique: This document is an executive order from Franklin D. Roosevelt amending the Foreign Service Regulations of the United States. It authorizes the Secretary of State to issue general instructions related to civil vessels, aircraft, seamen, and their documents. The order also cancels several sections of the Foreign Service Regulations. Given the subject matter, the document has minimal ideological content. It primarily concerns administrative and procedural matters within the realm of foreign service and international navigation. Therefore, most axes should be scored as neutral. There's no indication of a shift in executive power, federalism, or any specific stance on national security vs. civil liberties, economic regulation, or social inclusion. The document does not address immigration directly or indirectly.
